-- Constancio Says Central Bank in Favor of `Permanent' Rescue Framework
-- B y   M e e r a   L o u i s
-- 2010-09-29T09:47:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/constancio-says-central-bank-in-favor-of-permanent-rescue-framework.html
European Central Bank Vice
President Vitor Constancio said the central bank is in favour of
a “permanent framework” to support member states if needed.   “We are in favor of having a permanent framework that
deals with problems of this nature without going into details,”
Constancio told Bloomberg News at a conference in Brussels
today. “To have in place the possibility of dealing with
situations where countries may need assistance with
conditionality of course as it has been the case.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Meera Louis in Brussels at 
